{"id":"project-LICHEN-6y2k","title":"announce.c: register_app_data_observer can silently clear all observers","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/announce.c
Lines: 371-381

In lichen_announce_register_app_data_observer() and _ex():

    k_mutex_lock(&observer_mutex, K_FOREVER);
    if (cb == NULL) {
        memset(announce_observers, 0, sizeof(announce_observers));
        k_mutex_unlock(&observer_mutex);
        return 0;
    }

Passing NULL as the callback clears ALL observers. This is:
1. Undocumented in the header
2. Dangerous - a typo or uninitialized pointer could wipe all registrations
3. Inconsistent - passing NULL user_data is fine, but NULL cb has special meaning

The header says:
    lichen_announce_app_data_fn _Nonnull cb

The _Nonnull annotation suggests NULL is not allowed, but the implementation has special NULL handling.

Either:
1. Add explicit lichen_announce_unregister_all_observers() function
2. Document the NULL behavior
3. Return -EINVAL on NULL cb as the annotation suggests","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:52:32.305538Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:52:32.305565Z"}
